content:
Manage an Out-of-Sequence Endorsement

An out-of-sequence endorsement is a modification to a policy with an effective date that is earlier than the effective date of another endorsement already bound on the policy. All backdated changes are automatically applied on top of future policy versions within and across the policy terms.

For example, you issue a policy and add an endorsement 1 with an effective date of 7/1/2023. Now, if you create another endorsement transaction with an effective date of 3/1/2023, the transaction is out of sequence.

Once an out-of-sequence endorsement is performed on a policy, all future versions in the timeline of the policy are updated to reflect the change.

As part of the Out-of-Sequence Endorsement, you can:

Perform backdated modifications to a policy within and across the policy term.
Apply the backdated changes automatically to future versions.
Enable out-of-sequence endorsement for internal agents using lightning web component.
Generate the Out-of-Sequence Changed/Endorsed transaction for the period impacted due to out-of-sequence endorsement.

Prerequisites for Out-of-Sequence Endorsement
Configure an Out-of-Sequence Endorsement
Issue an Out-of-Sequence Endorsement Policy
Subscribe to the InsAsyncJobStatusNotification Event
Get the Status of an Async Out-of-Sequence Endorsement

You can enable out-of-sequence endorsement for up to five years in the past and up to 15 policy versions, or up to one year in future and up to three future policy versions.

Out-of-sequence endorsement works asynchronously after you initiate the policy issuance with the new modifications. After an out-of-sequence endorsement completes, an event is published.
title: Configuring Out-of-Sequence Endorsements in Salesforce Insurance
